        "priority": "high",
        "details": "All other tasks must be complete before this one. This is the final validation pass.\n\nSteps:\n\n1. Confirm branch: `git branch --show-current` must return `updates`.\n\n2. Full rebuild from clean environment:\n   ```\n   rm -rf .venv\n   python3.12 -m venv .venv\n   source .venv/bin/activate\n   pip install --require-hashes -r requirements.lock\n   ```\n\n3. Fresh DB extraction:\n   ```\n   rm -f test.db\n   python main.py extract --hubs KHI,DXB --mode easy --workers 4 --db test.db\n   ```\n   Verify: completes without hangs, no warnings unless expected, total row count looks sensible.\n\n4. Schema integrity checks:\n   ```\n   sqlite3 test.db \"SELECT sql FROM sqlite_master WHERE name='route_aircraft'\" | grep UNIQUE\n   sqlite3 test.db \"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM route_aircraft GROUP BY origin_id, dest_id, aircraft_id HAVING COUNT(*) > 1\"  # must return nothing\n   sqlite3 test.db \"PRAGMA foreign_keys\"  # must return 1\n   sqlite3 test.db \"SELECT * FROM extract_metadata\"  # must have reputation, ci, game_mode, etc\n   ```\n\n5. Import a real fleet and routes CSV, verify convert_csv mappings work:\n   ```\n   python convert_csv.py sample_am4_routes.csv\n   python main.py fleet import --file fleet.csv --db test.db\n   python main.py routes import --file my_routes.csv --db test.db\n   ```\n\n6. Re-extract and confirm `total_planes_owned` is derived from my_fleet:\n   ```\n   python main.py extract --hubs KHI --db test.db 2>&1 | grep -i 'planes_owned'\n   sqlite3 test.db \"SELECT value FROM extract_metadata WHERE key='total_planes_owned'\"\n   ```\n\n7. Recommendations sanity check:\n   ```\n   python main.py recommend --hub KHI --budget 500000000 --top 10 --db test.db\n   ```\n   Verify both days_be_avg and days_be_best columns appear.\n\n8. Dashboard smoke test:\n   ```\n   python main.py dashboard --db test.db &\n   sleep 2\n   # Token is printed at startup - capture it\n   curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8000/ | head -c 200   # should return HTML\n   curl -s --max-time 2 http://$(hostname -I | awk '{print $1}'):8000/ 2>&1  # should fail (localhost-only)\n   # Test token enforcement\n   curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/fleet/delete -d fleet_id=1 -w \"%{http_code}\" -o /dev/null -s  # should return 401\n   kill %1\n   ```\n\n9. Docker smoke test:\n   ```\n   docker build -t am4-audit-final .\n   docker run --rm am4-audit-final id  # uid=1000(appuser)\n   docker run --rm am4-audit-final which gcc  # empty\n   docker compose up -d\n   sleep 10\n   curl http://127.0.0.1:8000/  # should work\n   docker compose down\n   ```\n\n10. Static analysis pass:\n    - `grep -rn \"except Exception:\" extractors/ | grep -v \"as exc\" | grep -v \"continue.*log\"` - should be empty or minimal\n    - `grep -rn \"host=.0.0.0.0.\" main.py` - should be empty (default is 127.0.0.1 now)\n    - `grep -rn \"reload=True\" main.py` - should only be via args.reload\n    - `grep -rn 'datetime(.now., .\\-.\\{.*\\}.days.' dashboard/` - should be empty (all parameterized)\n    - `grep -rn 'AIRCRAFT_MAP.*verify' convert_csv.py` - should be empty\n\n11. Run the aircraft mapping verifier: `python scripts/verify_aircraft_map.py` - exit 0.\n\n12. Check git log on this branch is clean:\n    ```\n    git log --oneline main..updates\n    ```\n    Each commit should be a logical unit from this task list. Squash/reorder via `git rebase -i` if needed.\n\n13. Push the branch:\n    ```\n    git push origin updates\n    ```\n\n14. Open a PR (if the user wants) OR leave as a branch ready for review.\n\nSuperpowers: Use `finishing-a-development-branch` skill to drive the merge decision. Present the user with options: merge to main, open PR for review, or keep branch for further iteration. Use `verification-before-completion` to make sure every test above actually passes before declaring the task complete.",
        "testStrategy": "Every check in the Details section must pass. Specifically: (a) fresh rebuild succeeds, (b) extraction produces expected row counts with no duplicates, (c) dashboard loads and token auth enforces, (d) LAN binding is blocked by default, (e) Docker image runs as non-root with no build tools, (f) aircraft mappings verify cleanly, (g) CHANGELOG matches the commits on the branch, (h) no regressions in any dashboard page.",
        "subtasks": []
      }
